  "title": "Livecode Server on DigitalOcean",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "2e7caae0a337f971",
      "text": "The following instructions are thanks to Mike Bonner and describe how to get [[Livecode Server]] running on [[DigitalOcean]]:"
    },
    {
      "type": "video",
      "id": "583c09e8d8b84927",
      "text": "VIMEO 131920147\nA quick rough and ready tutorial about how to set up your own [[Livecode Server]] and [[Apache]] set up on Digital Ocean.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "html",
      "id": "6a1a2bfee0e9a4a1",
      "text": "<H3>Fetch and Install LiveCode Server"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "6eb8c5758a209628",
      "text": "1) Create your Droplet. Choose LAMP 14.04 (Ubuntu) so you don't have to mess with setting up [[Apache]] and all by hand. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "c6d9d1a478f15284",
      "text": "2) Fetch Livecode. After [[Droplet]] creation, log into the server with ssh in the [[terminal]] used [[wget]] to grab the 64bit version of lc server 7.0.6. "
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "308ccc1432f83382",
      "text": "wget http://downloads.livecode.com/livecode/7_0_6/LiveCodeCommunityServer-7_0_6_rc_3-Linux-x86_64.zip"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "0de250892fd496dc",
      "text": "Alternatively you can use [[Digital Ocean]]s built in web console to issue terminal commands on the server through the web interface."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "53e974187bb7568a",
      "text": "3) Install [[unzip]]:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "16add05187abe1ac",
      "text": "apt-get install unzip"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "fa1cb693a9dc7da1",
      "text": "4) [[unzip]] the file (to expand the contents):"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "321e2e8f22eda08e",
      "text": "unzip <lc server filename>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "ef533d1e691e28f8",
      "text": "5) Make it executable the server file executable so you can launch it as a programme and not edit it as text:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "ed38f32c70b6fb36",
      "text": "chmod 755 livecode-community-server"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "2782e7ad36fc8b90",
      "text": "6) Move the files to the correct location (you could have moved the zipped file then could unzipped them there):"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "944147663e23c930",
      "text": "mv livecode-community-server /usr/lib/cgi-bin\nmv externals /usr/lib/cgi-bin\nmv drivers /usr/lib/cgi-bin"
    },
    {
      "type": "html",
      "id": "242970b808a1a078",
      "text": "<H3>Configure Apache"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "eca204be058a56f0",
      "text": "7) Enable the actions and cgi mods:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "ea47fd446133cb52",
      "text": "a2enmod actions\na2enmod cgi"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "094fa7c9ed1fe3a9",
      "text": "8) Edit the [[Apache]] .conf file:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "6053bd84d5ab916d",
      "text": "cd /etc/apache2/sites-enabled\nnano 000-default.conf"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "07e531771457df51",
      "text": "9) In the editor I added the 2 required lines as follows right before the end </virtualhost> line:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "45e1685fc33d4589",
      "text": "Action lc-script /cgi-bin/livecode-community-server\nAddHandler lc-script .lc"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d41481db39b39d87",
      "text": "I did NOT uncomment the line that says to include the serve-cgi-bin.conf"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d1138e365c515f45",
      "text": "ctrl-x yes to save, enter to keep the file name (make sure you don't change it). "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "eb5751be1f85c055",
      "text": "10) Restart your [[Apache]] server:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "0894435af481a1f7",
      "text": "service apache2 restart"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "1f9fade8f6ddf0b9",
      "text": "You may get a message on restart about not being able to reliably determine the servers domain name, depending on how things are currently set up."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "150ebeeec33f80bf",
      "text": "11) Add a test script to see if [[Apache]] is serving up [[LiveCode]] scripts as cgi's. Create a simple file:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "d8698c480b3cba06",
      "text": "nano -w /var/www/html/test.lc"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "48100bd36098d45d",
      "text": "and paste into it the following script:"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "623975c7629ac052",
      "text": "<?lc\n  put random(542545)\n?>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "dab7f85e39ca1b00",
      "text": "Then I went to the droplets ip..\nhttp://xxx.xxx.xxx.xx/test.lc and voila' it works."
    },
    {
      "type": "html",
      "id": "b80e282ed57053a4",
